to like that guy,

00:42:45.020 --> 00:42:47.820
but I hate him now, because he
runs a company in Nevada that

00:42:47.820 --> 00:42:51.900
just made it almost
impossible to get solar,

00:42:51.900 --> 00:42:55.240
because he has a
fossil fuel company.

00:42:55.240 --> 00:42:58.230
He made it almost impossible
for somebody in Nevada, which

00:42:58.230 --> 00:43:01.150
is all sun and desert,
to put up solar panels

00:43:01.150 --> 00:43:05.520
and get paid for it from the
state to sell back to energy.

00:43:05.520 --> 00:43:06.580
And they're doing this.

00:43:06.580 --> 00:43:07.580
This is their business model.

00:43:07.580 --> 00:43:09.330
They know they can't do
it on a national level.

00:43:09.330 --> 00:43:11.121
So they are going state
by state and trying

00:43:11.121 --> 00:43:15.280
to make the right thing to do
very difficult for well-meaning

00:43:15.280 --> 00:43:15.780
people.

00:43:15.780 --> 00:43:18.760
So we need to
fight them and also

00:43:18.760 --> 00:43:20.610
get legislation to
make it easy for people

00:43:20.610 --> 00:43:22.000
to do the right thing.

00:43:22.000 --> 00:43:26.520
And also, the impact of a
film is really powerful.

00:43:26.520 --> 00:43:27.780
We just have anecdotal stuff.

00:43:27.780 --> 00:43:30.190
But I was a judge at
Sundance this last year.

00:43:30.190 --> 00:43:32.312
And a guy was coming
to the bathroom

00:43:32.312 --> 00:43:33.270
rushing to get my seat.

00:43:33.270 --> 00:43:36.800
And some guy says, I just saw
"Racing Extinction" last year.

00:43:36.800 --> 00:43:37.600
It changed my life.

00:43:37.600 --> 00:43:38.230
I said, how so?

00:43:38.230 --> 00:43:41.620
He said, well, I had two
big cattle operations.

00:43:41.620 --> 00:43:43.910
I just got rid of both of them.

00:43:43.910 --> 00:43:46.870
And so films are a
really powerful tool.

00:43:46.870 --> 00:43:48.470
Tell your friends
to see the film.

00:43:48.470 --> 00:43:51.410
It's really important, because
you can sit there and talk

00:43:51.410 --> 00:43:54.150
about to your cleaning
lady about the importance

00:43:54.150 --> 00:43:56.810
of the environment that
it's really important what

00:43:56.810 --> 00:43:57.810
you do around the house.

00:43:57.810 --> 00:43:59.601
But you see a film like
"Racing Extinction"

00:43:59.601 --> 00:44:03.000
or I don't know, "Chasing Ice,"
or any other environmental

00:44:03.000 --> 00:44:05.146
films that are out
there, you don't

00:44:05.146 --> 00:44:06.270
have to explain it anymore.

00:44:06.270 --> 00:44:07.130
Buy them a copy.

00:44:07.130 --> 00:44:11.790
Give it to them with their
bi-weekly check or whatever.

00:44:11.790 --> 00:44:15.600
And one thing
about-- Ric O'Barry,

00:44:15.600 --> 00:44:17.410
who was the hero
of the first movie.

